<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-seS0g1DJ26wD2fk8JaaEhQ" name="viability_assessment,_2HXboDDHEdyz_pzDMsV8FQ" guid="-seS0g1DJ26wD2fk8JaaEhQ" changeDate="2008-09-22T02:10:10.000-0700" version="v.2">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This artifact documents the findings, risks and recommendations which are the results of performing a Viability&#xD;
    Assessment. A finding (and the associated risks) could be anything that is likely to impact the delivery of the&#xD;
    solution such as:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The ability to meet the solutions requirements.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The availability of the right skills.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The stakeholder acceptance of the technical elements of the proposed solution.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The ability to meet the schedule and budgetary constraints defined for the solution.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Lack of reusable elements in the solution.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></mainDescription>
  <keyConsiderations>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Consider the following when performing a Viability Assessment:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        A Viability Assessment can be performed either as part of a formal Quality Assurance review or on a more &quot;ad-hoc&quot;&#xD;
        basis when stakeholders or project management have raised concerns outside the normal review cycle.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Use any available checklists as a starter set of questions to ask.&amp;nbsp; Modify these before the review to suit the&#xD;
        needs of the particular project.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Ensure viability issues are clearly stated and there is an action plan in place to address them before presenting&#xD;
        the final report.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Ensure people who will be interviewed are briefed beforehand as to the purpose of the assessment so that they can&#xD;
        prepare the right material.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        When interviewing people as part of an assessment try to use neutral language as much as possible, do not use&#xD;
        language which could be construed as apportioning blame.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        It is better to raise critical issues early, when they can be resolved, rather than blindly following a schedule&#xD;
        that leads the project team down the wrong path.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The assessment needs to balance risks against costs, remaining sensitive to the broader issues of project success.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Viability Assessments can be difficult and sensitive.&amp;nbsp; The reviewer needs to be a persuasive communicator who&#xD;
        can raise and discuss sensitive issues.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></keyConsiderations>
  <purpose>This artifact is created as a result of performing a Viability Assessment. Its purpose is to record the findings of that&#xD;
assessment, the risks associated with the findings and the recommendations made to mitigate against those risks.</purpose>
  <impactOfNotHaving>Not having this work product increases the risk of a system being late, incomplete, or over budget.</impactOfNotHaving>
  <reasonsForNotNeeding>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This artifact is typically not needed for projects with a low risk of viability issues, such as:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Small projects&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Projects using an established infrastructure&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Projects using a widely accepted technical solution&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></reasonsForNotNeeding>
  <briefOutline>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This artifact should contain the following sections:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Approach&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        General Findings and Recommendations&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li style=&quot;LIST-STYLE-TYPE: none&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Findings&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Identified Risks&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Recommended Action Plans&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Risk Ranking Worksheet&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Architecture Checklist&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Recommendation for Next Review&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></briefOutline>
  <representationOptions>The Viability Assessment can be delivered in presentation format or as a formal report.</representationOptions>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription>
